<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kashira}}}} is a sentence ending particle mainly used by women and usually is translated as "I wonder".
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kashira}}}} can indicate uncertainty

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{mechanism^contraption}}no@KJ{{use}}i@KJ{{direction}},go@KJ{{exist}}deirasshaimasu@EM{{kashira}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if you are aquainted with how this machine works?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kashira}}}} can mark a question to oneself

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{mou@KJ{{homecoming}}ttemoiino@EM{{kashira}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if it's OK if I leave now?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
@EM{{@HI{{kashira}}}} can indicate a hope or a muted request

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{konpyu-ta-}}no@KJ{{use}}i@KJ{{direction}},@KJ{{teach}}eteitadakeru@EM{{kashira}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I wonder if you could teach me how to operate this computer?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

